# list-toolkit — AI Agent Rules

## Project identity

list-toolkit is a zero-dependency ESM JavaScript library providing list-based data structures: doubly and singly linked circular lists, caches (LRU, LFU, FIFO, random), heaps (min, leftist, skew), queues, stacks, splay trees, and null-terminated list utilities. Works in Node.js, Bun, Deno, and browsers.

## Critical rules

- **ESM-only.** `'use strict'` at the top of every source file.
- **No runtime dependencies.** Never add packages to `dependencies`. Only `devDependencies` are allowed.
- **Do not modify or delete test expectations** without understanding why they changed.
- **Do not add comments or remove comments** unless explicitly asked.

## Code style

- Prettier: 160 char width, single quotes, no bracket spacing, no trailing commas, arrow parens "avoid".
- 2-space indentation (`.editorconfig`).
- Imports at top of file. No dynamic imports unless necessary.

## Architecture quick reference

- All lists are **circular**: the last node links back to the head.
- **DLL** uses customizable `nextName`/`prevName` link properties (default: `next`/`prev`).
- **SLL** uses a customizable `nextName` link property (default: `next`).
- **Hosted lists** (`List`, `ValueList`, `SList`, `ValueSList`) use a `HeadNode` sentinel.
- **External (headless) lists** (`ExtList`, `ExtValueList`, `ExtSList`, `ExtValueSList`) point into an existing circular list.
- **Value lists** wrap values in `ValueNode` containers. **Node lists** use link properties directly on user objects.
- **Caches** are built on `ValueList` + `Map`. All share the same API: `has`, `find`/`get`, `register`/`set`, `remove`/`delete`, `clear`.
- **Heaps** support `less` or `compare` for ordering. `MinHeap` is array-based; `LeftistHeap` and `SkewHeap` are merge heaps.
- **SplayTree** is a self-adjusting BST with `insert`, `find`, `remove`, `split`, `join`.
- Method aliases are created via `addAlias`/`addAliases` from `meta-utils.js`.

## Verification commands

- `npm test` — run the full test suite (tape-six)
- `node tests/test-<name>.js` — run a single test file directly
- `npm run test:bun` — run with Bun
- `npm run test:deno` — run with Deno
- `npm run build` — Babel transpile `src/` → `cjs/`

## File layout

- Source: `src/` (ESM), `cjs/` (generated CJS, gitignored)
- Top-level re-exports: `src/list.js`, `src/cache.js`, `src/heap.js`, etc.
- Implementations: `src/list/`, `src/slist/`, `src/cache/`, `src/heap/`, `src/tree/`
- Tests: `tests/test-*.js`
- Wiki docs: `wiki/` (git submodule)

## When reading the codebase

- Start with `ARCHITECTURE.md` for the module map and dependency graph.
- Wiki markdown files in `wiki/` contain detailed usage docs and API references.
- `list/nodes.js` and `slist/nodes.js` are the foundational modules.
